College_Heading: Linfield College, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Founded in 1858, Linfield College is a private, co-educational institution located in McMinnville, Oregon, USA. It has two campuses and the other campus at Portland houses the Linfield-Good Samaritan School of Nursing offering nursing programs to non-traditional and adult students to complete their bachelor’s degree. The school changed its name to Linfield University in July with a College of Arts and Sciences, School of Business and School of Nursing. The college primarily offers undergraduate degrees with over 50 majors and 2 master’s degrees for higher education in US. Linfield Online and Continuing Education offers fully online programs to working adults. The institution is accredited by the Northwest Commission on Colleges and Universities.

College_Heading: Baldwin Wallace University [BW]: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Baldwin Wallace University is an independent, liberal arts and science university. It is situated in Berea, Ohio, United States. A Methodist businessman John Baldwin founded the University as an institution in 1845. BW is renowned because of its wide range of programs across the disciplines like education, business, neuroscience, and music. BW Conservatory owns the award for the country's largest Bach School Festival. Interestingly, WBWC radio channel at the campus is popular all over the Cleveland region.

College_Heading: Beedie School of Business: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: The Beedie School of Business is a leading institute part of Simon Fraser University. It is the only institute in its region to have been awarded with EQUIS Quality award from the European Federation for Management Development (EFMD) and accredited by the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business (AACSB). Both the recognitions place the Beedie School of Business to be among the top 1% of business schools worldwide. The school is the pioneer of establishing Executive MBA in Canada. Since then, the school has introduced various other programs such as Management of Technology MBA, the Master of Science in Finance, full-time and part-time MBA. Overall, about 16 UG and PG programs are offered at SFU Beedie.

College_Heading: UBC Sauder School of Business: Rankings, Courses, Fees, Campus, Admissions 2024, Scholarships & Placements
College_Summary: Established in 1956, UBC Sauder School of Business is an affiliation of University of British Columbia. The prestigious institution is ranked number-one for its business programs in Canada. As an international student interested in business and management, you get to choose from 22 programs at UBC Sauder. The business school takes immense pride in its 47,000 graduates and more than 4,800 students who enrolled in 2023.

College_Name: School of Management Science, University of Quebec at Montreal, Montreal
College_Heading: School of Management Science, University of Quebec at Montreal, Canada: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Acceptance Rate, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: School of Management Science, University of Quebec is a public college, affiliated to the University of Quebec, which is solely dedicated to courses related to management sciences. It has a total enrolment of around 35,000 students, with international students from over 90 countries all around the globe to study in Canada. The University of Quebec at Montreal observes an acceptance rate of 50%, and is therefore considered to be moderately selective.
